article.headline: Harvard 78, Dartmouth 65
article.story: BOSTON (AP) -- Jim Goffredo scored a career-high 33 points including seven 3-pointers on Saturday to lead Harvard to a 78-65 win over Dartmouth. Brian Cusworth added 15 points and Matt Stehle scored 14 and had eight rebounds, eight assists and three blocks. Michael Giovacchini led Dartmouth (2-10, 0-1 Ivy League) with 19 points and Alex Barnett scored 13. The Crimson (9-5, 1-0) were 17 of 23 from the free throw line compared to 5 of 6 for Dartmouth. Harvard also outrebounded the Big Green 41-27. Goffredo paced the Crimson to a 38-27 lead at halftime with five 3-pointers in the first half. He then capped a 10-4 run in the second half with a pair of free throws with 12:21 left, giving the Crimson a 50-34 lead. Harvard extended the lead to a game-high 65-45 on Evan Harris' jumper with 7:30 left.
